Frontend Development Second Monthly Exam

This is a multiple choice question based exam designed to assess your understanding of HTML and CSS in frontend development.

1. What utility class adds horizontal padding in Tailwind?

2. What value makes an element a grid container?

3. Which class makes an element responsive to screen size?

4. What is the purpose of a media query?

5. What is the default value of the `flex-direction` property in Flexbox?

6. What does `git init` do?

7. What does the `meta` viewport tag do?

8. What is GitHub?

9. Which property defines the ability for a flex item to grow if necessary?

10. What command stages all changes for commit?

11. How can you create a 3-column grid with equal widths?

12. What value of `justify-content` will space the items evenly with space around them?

13. Which media query is correct for screens smaller than 768px?

14. Which unit is relative to the width of the viewport?

15. Which property aligns flex items horizontally in a flex container?

16. What does `bg-blue-500` represent in Tailwind CSS?

17. What does `grid-column: 1 / 3;` do?

18. Which property sets the size of grid columns?

19. Which property is used to define rows in a CSS grid container?

20. How do you make a flex container wrap its items into multiple lines?
